The paper proposes coding techniques for DNA-based data storage systems, which involves information theory and data structures. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with error correction, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing results, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
